Premaxilla with two tooth rows; outer row with 3-4, rarely 2, pentacuspid teeth with central cusp larger; inner row teeth 5, rarely 6, gradually decreasing in length from first to fourth teeth, last tooth considerably smaller, with 5-9 cusps and central cusp longer and broader than other cusps. Three to 5 maxillary teeth, with 5-7 cusps, central cusp slightly longer. Four or 5 anterior-most dentary teeth larger, with 7 cusps, followed by 1-2 middle sized tooth with 5-7 cusps, and 6-7 teeth with 1-3 cusps or conical in shape; central cusp in all teeth two to three times longer and broader than remaining cusps. Cusp tips slightly curved posteriorly and towards inside of mouth (
Fig. 2
).
